<span id="freeTextContainer15775865332416553878">He wrote that by personally observing horses in the wild, he learned to &quot;listen&quot; to their non-verbal &quot;language&quot;; that when horses understood that they can trust you, they will decide to be with you. Roberts registered as his term for &quot;hooking on&quot;, the phrase &quot;Join~Up&quot;, in which a trainer negotiates with an untamed horse to form a voluntary relationship with him</span>
  <span id="freeText15775865332416553878" style="display:none">He wrote that by personally observing horses in the wild, he learned to "listen" to their non-verbal "language"; that when horses understood that they can trust you, they will decide to be with you. Roberts registered as his term for "hooking on", the phrase "Join~Up", in which a trainer negotiates with an untamed horse to form a voluntary relationship with him</span>
